         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Recto and verso are inverted in <bibl><title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/><citedRange>366</citedRange></bibl>: "[w]ritten in medium ductus, and quite clearly preserved on the verso [i.e. recto here], it is badly abraded on most of the recto [i.e. verso here], where there are the only two Kuchean words. The rest of the manuscript is Sanskrit. It can be seen to have been a five line manuscript."</note></p>
